-- Accenture says cooperating with China anti-trust regulator
-- By Paul Carsten
-- Wed Aug 06, 2014 05:45AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, Aug 6 (Reuters) - Accenture PLC <ACN.N> said on Wednesday it was providing client information to a Chinese regulator, which is investigating Microsoft Corp <MSFT.O> for anti-trust violations.

The State Administration for Industry and Commerce (SAIC) conducted new raids on Microsoft and Accenture, its partner in China, the agency said on its website on Wednesday. [ID:nL4N0QC25T] "We can confirm that, as required by Chinese laws, we are cooperating with investigators of the State Administration for Industry and Commerce and help provide them with certain information related to one of our clients," Accenture Greater China said in an e-mailed statement. It declined to provide further information.